===Etymology===
{{unk.}}. Many theories exist, all of which lack supporting evidence.<ref>{{R:Dictionary.com|copacetic}}</ref> One theory is that the term originated among African Americans in the Southern US in the early 20th century or late 19th century—perhaps (as jazz historians think) specifically in the jargon of [[w:Bill Robinson|Bill "Bojangles" Robinson]].<ref>Mark Knowles, ''Tap Roots: The Early History of Tap Dancing'' (ISBN 0786412674), page 239</ref> Another is that it has its origins in Louisiana French, Italian{{,}} or Chinook Jargon.<ref>David L Gold, ''Studies in Etymology and Etiology'', pages 60-61</ref>

